l.#text:
For this law is not of now or yesterday, but is eternal . . . this I
								was not likely to infringe through fear of the
								pride of any man;

note.#text:
The defence in such cases is: 1 that the
						previous oath was taken as a result of fraud or compulsion;
						2 that you did not mean what you said.

l.#text:
,
								they were ready to accept gifts and to be persuaded by
								words;
